		"body": "<p>Some of the many ways to do Omote Gyaku with a bit of a twist.</p>\n<table class=\"table table-striped\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>Standard ('Gary Style')</td>\n<td>Check ukes hand and step back at 45 degrees, prising his grip off with your forearm. Step in and jerk his arm up to release his grip. Turn your body away as you fold his wrist to take him down.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Passive ('Joe Style')</td>\n<td>Step diagonally back into ichimonji like kamae to initiate move.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Mori No Yokai ('Iyesten Style')</td>\n<td>Check hand and step diagonally back at 45 degrees to initiate move. Lift his arm off your gi and step forwards as you apply the lock, taking him down in the space you created by stepping back.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Explosive 1</td>\n<td>Sink your weight down as you rip his arm off your shirt as usual. Turn your body 180 degrees or more, fast, as you twist his arm around. It will feel like more of a 'throw'.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Explosive 2</td>\n<td>As punch comes in, step back at 45 degrees into a low hoko no kamae. Grab his punching hand and pivot 180 degrees or more etc. This should be quite strongly aerial.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Up./Down. Chi. Takeori.</td>\n<td>Lift his arm up. Step in close to him and apply the omote gyaku principally in a downwards direction. It will be felt on his wrist more and if done right will force him to bend his knees and go directly down.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Kogoroshi/Ogoroshi</td>\n<td>Uke Kogoroshi and/or Ogoroshi</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Zenpo Tobi Kaiten</td>\n<td>Esentailly an exadgerated Mori No Yokai style Omote Gyaku: Check his hand and step back at 45 degrees as usual but into a&nbsp;<strong>very&nbsp;</strong>low ichimonji. Then jump forwards, fast, far and hard with a zenpo tobi kaithen, while still holding his hand, slamming it into the ground as you land. Continue to roll out.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Opposite step</td>\n<td>Cover his grabbing hand with your hand as usual. Instead of stepping diagonally back and across in the direction towards the side that is grabbed, step diagonally back and to the other side, while turning your body away. It will feel a bit like the start of ura gyaku. Take him down.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>&nbsp;Fist</td>\n<td>This time from punch. As punch comes in step to the side (hira no kamae) and let it travel past you as you catch it. (You should have the palm of your hand touching the back of his hand, controlling it. Roll his fingers up and compress his fingers/knuckles/wrist into his forearm. A bit like takeori.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Arcus' Gyoko Ryu Special</td>\n<td>Check hand. Boshi to pectoral with other hand. Apply pressure to pectoral as you apply omote gyaku witih the other hand. Kick him on the same side as the omote gyaku in the ribs. Fully apply gyaku and take down. Stomp on chest/head etc to finish.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Kukishinden Ryu style from punch</td>\n<td>Punch comes in. Jodan Uke, but hold hand at end. Step in and punch at his eyes with other hand. Apply omote gyaku on captive hand.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>[Omote Onikudaki]</td>\n<td>Punch comes in. Jodan Uke with left hand. Step in and place right hand under his punching arm into oni kudaki position. Pull down with thumb joint etc and oni kudaki.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>[Ura Onikudaki]</td>\n<td>Punch comes in. Jodan Uke with left hand. Do haymaker style punch with right hand, and continue past his face, with your hand coming to rest in the oni kudaki position in his elbow pit. Row oni kudaki. Keep it tight.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>",
