		"body": "<ul>\n<li><span style=\"line-height: 1.3em;\">Be clear minded. Aim to primarily not hurt the uke, secondarily do the technique correctly.</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"line-height: 1.3em;\">Be aware of ukes body and have authority over it.</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"line-height: 1.3em;\">Project an attacking intention when you are uke.</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"line-height: 1.3em;\">Don't wrestle. Use skill at all times. Slow it down if you need to, but try not to pause.</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"line-height: 1.3em;\">Always finish a technique, even if it goes wrong.</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"line-height: 1.3em;\">Always be attentive, thoughtful. Go through things in your mind as much as possible before you find they are happening and you are not ready.</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"line-height: 1.3em;\">Bear in mind kyusho and go for them.</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"line-height: 1.3em;\">Do techniques with right timing and spacing.</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"line-height: 1.3em;\">Bear in mind kamae as you do techniques.</span></li>\n</ul>",
