		"body": "<h2>Arcus's ura gyaku variations</h2>\n<p>In and up, out and down</p>\n<p>Do lock on non punching arm: punch comes in. step on inside. check punching arm with trailing hand. grab non punching arm with front hand. your thumb should go over the top of the back of his palm to the inside of his palm. lift it up and piroette in, putting lock on. take to mat.</p>\n<h2>Grab escapes with weapons</h2>\n<h3><span style=\"line-height: 1.3em;\">Body grab (single or double)</span></h3>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"line-height: 1.3em;\">Lift bo up, smacking both his arms up. Then bo to his neck or chest. Bo is parallel to ground at all times.</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"line-height: 1.3em;\">Slam bo down, smacking his arms down. Watch for head collision. Bo to his neck.</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"line-height: 1.3em;\">Bring bo (or knife) across top of his wrist, and cross you arms, grabbing other side of bo or knife with other hand. make scissor motion to put it on and apply pressure downwards.</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"line-height: 1.3em;\">As above, but over his elbow. Use it to put on a sort of musha dori.</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"line-height: 1.3em;\">As above, but slightly higher than his elbow, against his tricep. Hug his arm to your chest as you put it on tight and put on arm bar as you put pressure on his tricep.</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"line-height: 1.3em;\">Step back into seigan with bo, pressing tip into his throat. With arm furthest up bo, release bo, and put ura gyaku on his hand.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<h3><span style=\"line-height: 1.3em;\">Arm grab</span></h3>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"line-height: 1.3em;\">Hold knife in reverse grip as he grabs that knife holding arm. step back and put the knife in from outside to inside. apply pressure with back of knife</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"line-height: 1.3em;\">(There was some other one where you jab the knife into the ball and socket of his shoulder/back joint as you put on ogyaku)</span></li>\n</ul>",
