		"body": "<p>In this lesson we went back over the kihon happo counters learnt in the previous lesson, and went on to do the ones left.</p>\n<h2>Torite Kihon Goho</h2>\n<h3>Omote Gyaku</h3>\n<p><strong>Reversal 2: Katate Oten out, apply arm bar on exit.</strong></p>\n<h4>Musha Dori</h4>\n<p><strong>Reversal 2: As your kuzushi is about to collapse, sink down into hamza and pivot 360 degrees while keeping back straight. As you do this, you should allow your back leg to trail out backwards to trip him as you push on his opposite side shoulder.</strong></p>\n<div class=\"tips\">\n<ul>\n<li>If your foot is on your ukes, you can use your toes to push down hard on his foot kyusho.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>",
