		"body": "<h2>Koshi Kihon Sanpo</h2>\n<h3>Ichimonji No Kata</h3>\n<p>Uke Punch. Tori Jodan Uke: Strike downwards slightly to rotate him and open his neck more. Tori omote shuto. Aim for Stomach 9: Push neck muscle out of the way and strike to nerve. Power with body.</p>\n<p><strong>Reversal: Uke Punch. Tori Jodan Uke. As tori does shuto, uke does jodan uke. Can be looped for practice.</strong></p>\n<h3>Hicho No Kata</h3>\n<p>Uke low punch. Tori (in hicho) does low block - <em>Down</em>. Optionally hook/grab arm. Kick to armpit - <em>Up</em>. Ura Shuto to neck/back of head - <em>Down</em>.</p>\n<p><strong>Reversal: Uke low punch. Tori low block. As Toris kick comes in, uke grabs it and performs (omote?) gyaku on ukes foot.</strong></p>\n<h3>Jumonji No Kata</h3>\n<p>Uke punch to face. Tori block, boshi to armpit, hand to eyes: INTENTION. Repeat on other side and end in Kosei. (Which also appears loosely at two other points in this kata)</p>\n<p><strong>Reversal: Uke punch to face. Tori block. As tori blocks, or goes for boshi, uke sinks weight and does a low block motion with the arm. Uke punches again with other arm, or uses same arm to do a strike/takedown.</strong></p>\n<h2>Torite Kihon Goho</h2>\n<h3>Omote Gyaku</h3>\n<p>Uke grab lapel. Tori checks hand and rotates, applying armbar with elbow. <strong>Be sure you are affecting his wrist and loosening his grip.</strong>Tori drops weight, and tears grip off by lifting arms up. Tori adjusts grip slightly and rotates for takedown.</p>\n<p><strong>Reversal: Uke grab lapel. As tori tries to initiate lock, uke steps in so he is close to uke, standing behind him.</strong></p>\n<h3>Ura Gyaku</h3>\n<p>Uke grab lapel on toris left side. Tori checks hand with left hand, steps back and twists, reaching over with their right hand. <em>Dont grab, just pry off.</em> Tori then twists the other way, prying with their right hand, keeping the ukes hand on their chest. <em>Pause and feel the control if training.</em>Then armbar and down, or just down. Try to stop uke from rolling.</p>\n<p><strong>Reversal: Uke grab lapel. Tori steps back and twists, initiating lock. As tori does so, uke steps directly towards uke, striking with elbow to face. Then sink weight and strike down on chest with same elbow.</strong></p>\n<h3>Musha Dori</h3>\n<p>Kumiuchi. Take kuzushi (with kyusho if desired) as you step to the side and lift his arm away gently. Thrust your arm down and through <em>- towards weak point in ukes kamae - and rotate to be standing alongside uke as you stand up, lifing his arm up, putting the lock on, obliterating ukes balance. Kick to back leg, or pressure point on back leg.</em></p>\n<p><strong>Reversal: As uke tries to initiate lock, step back with the side (arm, leg) that he is trying to take the arm of. On the opposite side, lift his arm up, taking his balance. Step through him, making him collapse.</strong></p>\n<div class=\"tips\">\n<ul>\n<li>You can go forward to complete omote gyaku but be aware that you:</li>\n<ul>\n<li>Keep the wrist lock on. This is harder when his arm is not straight, so push him <em>Down.</em></li>\n<li>Watch out for a strike coming from his other arm.</li>\n</ul>\n<li>Diagonal stepping is from Koto Ryu. Gyoko ryu uses more lateral stepping, and is a bit more upright, as per the way Joe seems to move more often.</li>\n<li>All ninjutsu can techniques can be done with any of the five attitudes in the Godai. ie Even aggressive techniques can be done in wind, compassion, if you do not want to permanently injure your assailant.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>",
