		"body": "<h2>Sanshin Pointers</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"line-height: 1.3em;\">For uke, best not to punch from Doko. Doko is defensive - takes ages to punch from this.</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"line-height: 1.3em;\"><span style=\"line-height: 1.3em;\">Be sure to block correctly. With fist not wrist. (Wrist can sustain damage)</span></span></li>\n<li><span style=\"line-height: 1.3em;\"><span style=\"line-height: 1.3em;\"><span style=\"line-height: 1.3em;\">Don't lean back to get distance. Step further or wider or stand lower.</span></span></span></li>\n<li><span style=\"line-height: 1.3em;\"><span style=\"line-height: 1.3em;\"><span style=\"line-height: 1.3em;\"><span style=\"line-height: 1.3em;\">Try to keep hips at same level throughout</span></span></span></span></li>\n<li><span style=\"line-height: 1.3em;\"><span style=\"line-height: 1.3em;\"><span style=\"line-height: 1.3em;\"><span style=\"line-height: 1.3em;\"><span style=\"line-height: 1.3em;\">For Ka no Kata, consider dropping back with your striking hand actually in Doko</span></span></span></span></span></li>\n</ul>\n<h2>3 Types of block</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Uke: Soft Block</li>\n<li>Daken Uke: Striking Block</li>\n<li>Ukenagashi: Parrying / Redirecting Block</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Throws</h2>\n<h3>Hip Throw</h3>\n<p>Kumiuchi. Strong grip around his chest. step in low and close. Twist and push his grip away at inside of his elbow as you twist. Bum in, up. Lift him onto your back and drop. Stop his feet from hitting ground first for max effectiveness. Consider dropping your body onto his for an extremely heavy fall if necessary.</p>\n<p>Arm Throw (\"Seoe Nage?\")</p>\n<p>Similar to above but with his arm. Lift his arm over your shoulder, keep it straight. Lift him onto your back and drop etc</p>\n<h3>Stepping throw</h3>\n<p>Archetypical kneepit to kneepit and push over. Arcus emphasised: Pull him off balance first so you dont have to step around him, where you are not strong. Then, step inÂ aggressivelyÂ  literally displacing him from his space and making him fall.</p>\n<h3>Pain throw</h3>\n<p>Kumiuchi. Then unexpectedly grab the flesh around his sides with a powerful renishi. Turn as you drop to one knee, throwing him behind you.</p>\n<h2>Koto Ryu</h2>\n<p>Koto Ryu is characterised by lots of jumps, and has a back and forward feeling.</p>\n<h3>Koto Ryu Waza</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>You are walking toward each other. Jump at (past) him, and shuto to the neck</li>\n<li>You are walking toward each other. Boshi or koppo to side of ribcage: He should step his opposite leg out. Jump kick to the middle of upper thigh with your back leg to make him fall.</li>\n<li>You are walking toward each other. He goes to kick you. As before, jump and kick to his leg. (Non kicking leg goes back as kicking leg goes forward. Both feet land similtaneously).</li>\n<li>Uke lapel grab. Grab his neck muscles (trapezius) and control his hands/arms with your elbows. Hold and jump into his 'lap' as he remains standing. Punch to face/neck/head. Slides down his legs with your legs. Let go of his neck and bring your arms to his ankles. Control him here with hands and 1 foot. Kick to his upper torso with other foot to bring him down. Axe kick onto his groin or chest. Ushiro kaiten.</li>\n<li>Uke single hand lapel grab. Stike to back to corner of jaw as you step forward or backward with opposite leg. Lift him up with a kick to the groin, and before he comes all the way back down, palm to his chin.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Gyokko Ryu</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"line-height: 1.3em;\">Uke single hand grab. Check hand. Boshi to pectoral with other hand. Apply pressure to pectoral as you apply omote gyaku with the other hand. Kick him on the same side as the omote gyaku in the ribs. Fully apply gyaku and take down. Stomp on chest.</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"line-height: 1.3em;\">Uke single hand grab. Palm to chin. Start omote gyaku, kick to his tricep then fully apply to take down.</span></li>\n</ul>\n<h2><span style=\"line-height: 1.3em;\">Neck Kyusho</span></h2>\n<ul>\n<li>3 Fingers at collar bone hole. Push down and forwards.</li>\n<li>Frankensteins Bolt</li>\n<li>Large neck muscle. Grab it and pull it.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Â </p>",
