		"body": "<h2>Yin and Yang</h2>\n<p>Yin and Yang are used as part of accupuncture and shiatsu, the art of manipulating kyusho for positive health effects. This understanding can also be used for negative effects. Some kyusho provide a yin reaction - causing opponent to collapse in on himself - while others can provice a yang reaction - causing the opponent to tense up and unfurl, extending his posture in pain.</p>\n<table class=\"table table-striped\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>Chinese Name</td>\n<td>Yin&nbsp;</td>\n<td>&nbsp;Yang</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Japanese Name</td>\n<td>In</td>\n<td>Yo</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Colour</td>\n<td>Black</td>\n<td>White</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Sex</td>\n<td>Female</td>\n<td>Male</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Radiance</td>\n<td>Dark</td>\n<td>Light</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Temperature</td>\n<td>Cold</td>\n<td>Hot</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Direction</td>\n<td>In</td>\n<td>Out</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Relation</td>\n<td>Introvert</td>\n<td>Extrovert</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Manipulation</td>\n<td>Exhausting</td>\n<td>Compelling</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<h2>Commonly targeted pressure points in Ninjutsu</h2>\n<table class=\"table table-striped\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>Accupuncture Name</td>\n<td>Japanese Name</td>\n<td>Location</td>\n<td>Specific Effects</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td></td>\n<td>Ooko</td>\n<td>Neck - \"Frankenstein's Bolt\".</td>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Stomach 9</td>\n<td></td>\n<td>Neck - In line with Adam's Apple, and to the side; Where the pulse can be felt.</td>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Pericardium 6</td>\n<td></td>\n<td>Two finger-widths up from the bottom of the hand; the inside of the wrist.</td>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Lung 5</td>\n<td>Nagare</td>\n<td>Near top of forearm, on the outside.</td>\n<td>In/Yin</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td></td>\n<td>Nagare</td>\n<td>Near top of forearm, on the inside.</td>\n<td><span style=\"font-size: 11px; text-align: start;\">In/Yin</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td></td>\n<td><span style=\"font-size: 11px; text-align: start;\">Jakeen</span></td>\n<td>Middle of bicep; on its apex. Push the bicep apart from the top, to get to the point underneath directly.</td>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td></td>\n<td><span style=\"font-size: 11px; text-align: start;\">&nbsp;</span></td>\n<td>Armpit.</td>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n<td>The confluence where the thumb and index finger meet at the base of the palm. Right in there.</td>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n<td>A knees height above the knee, on the inside of the thigh. Strike up, hitting the point against the femur.</td>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td></td>\n<td>Kasumi</td>\n<td>Temple.</td>\n<td>&nbsp;Can cause disorientation.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n<td>Corner of jaw.</td>\n<td>&nbsp;An effective knockout point.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n<td>Philtrum.</td>\n<td>&nbsp;Pain and bleeding.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n<td>Top of skull, in the very middle.</td>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n<td>Base of skull.</td>\n<td>A very effective knockout point, but also very dangerous. Can cause death or paralysis with skull separating from spine.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n<td>Top of thigh.</td>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>",
